All right, guys,
Semanko's making a big payment, so...

252
00:16:42,037 --> 00:16:44,379
<i>We're looking for someone
who's carrying a lot of cash.</i>

253
00:16:56,184 --> 00:16:57,750
Okay, Phoenix, I just take a look.

254
00:16:57,858 --> 00:16:59,119
This guy looks like he's got

255
00:16:59,135 --> 00:17:01,032
<i>a couple hundred dollars
worth of rubles on him.</i>

256
00:17:01,051 --> 00:17:02,672
Definitely not Semanko.

257
00:17:02,673 --> 00:17:03,402
<i>Moving on.</i>

258
00:17:20,687 --> 00:17:23,182
We got dollars. We got euros,

259
00:17:23,195 --> 00:17:24,636
We've even got a little Turkish

260
00:17:24,656 --> 00:17:25,977
<i>Lira thrown in there but</i>

261
00:17:26,022 --> 00:17:28,879
doesn't look like anybody's buying more
than a couple drinks tonight.

262
00:17:31,450 --> 00:17:32,420
Wait, hold on, Oracle.

263
00:17:32,471 --> 00:17:35,206
That guy who just passed you
has a loaded Makarov under his jacket.

264
00:17:38,172 --> 00:17:38,972
Scratch that.

265
00:17:39,005 --> 00:17:40,580
We've got three guys with Makarovs.

266
00:17:40,636 --> 00:17:41,445
<i>Three guys.</i>

267
00:17:41,521 --> 00:17:42,545
<i>And the guy in the center</i>

268
00:17:42,553 --> 00:17:45,510
looks like he's got about $100,000 cold
around his waist.

269
00:17:45,647 --> 00:17:47,536
Think we found comrade Semanko.

270
00:17:47,638 --> 00:17:49,136
Sidewinder, do you have a 20 on him?

271
00:17:49,502 --> 00:17:50,472
Northeast corner,

272
00:17:50,509 --> 00:17:51,947
<i>near the V.I.P. Section.</i>

273
00:17:52,530 --> 00:17:53,841
Got it. I'm on my way.

274
00:17:54,198 --> 00:17:55,475
<i>Oracle? Keep him busy.</i>

275
00:18:00,066 --> 00:18:01,649
Please, watch where you're going.

276
00:18:01,734 --> 00:18:02,636
I'm sorry.

277
00:18:02,874 --> 00:18:04,321
You have my apologies.

278
00:18:04,423 --> 00:18:05,172
Then...

279
00:18:05,308 --> 00:18:07,810
a true gentleman would offer
to make it up to me.

280
00:18:07,844 --> 00:18:09,656
What exactly do you have in mind?

281
00:18:09,711 --> 00:18:10,478
Saskia.

282
00:18:16,344 --> 00:18:18,685
My apologies. My wife she's...

283
00:18:18,754 --> 00:18:20,115
a bit of a whore.

284
00:18:23,286 --> 00:18:24,341
Tracker's hot.

285
00:18:24,443 --> 00:18:25,362
<i>Copy that.</i>

286
00:18:25,472 --> 00:18:26,134
Merlin?

287
00:18:26,183 --> 00:18:27,745
<i>He just headed
into the V.I.P room.</i>

288
00:18:28,048 --> 00:18:29,091
Check support teams.

289
00:18:29,154 --> 00:18:31,537
I want 'em ready to move
as soon as we know Will's location.

290
00:18:31,630 --> 00:18:33,008
Copy that. They're on standby.

291
00:18:33,145 --> 00:18:35,408
<i>Ms. Espinosa. A pleasure.</i>

292
00:18:35,833 --> 00:18:38,539
- Where's my payment?
- It's all here.

293
00:18:39,509 --> 00:18:40,922
Count it if you wish.

294
00:18:41,263 --> 00:18:42,225
Where is Tippin?

295
00:18:42,450 --> 00:18:43,761
Thought I'd make your life easy.

296
00:18:43,879 --> 00:18:45,514
You'll find him in room 147.

297
00:18:47,710 --> 00:18:50,253
Sidewinder, Oracle, do you copy?
Will's in the building.

298
00:18:50,431 --> 00:18:52,040
Copy that. Right behind you.

299
00:18:59,970 --> 00:19:01,349
Would you two come with us, please.

300
00:19:10,196 --> 00:19:11,252
Are you okay?

301
00:19:16,077 --> 00:19:17,797
Hope I'm not interrupting anything.

302
00:19:20,682 --> 00:19:22,231
How good is your operative?

303
00:19:22,758 --> 00:19:24,494
We'll find out soon enough.

304
00:19:30,857 --> 00:19:31,725
She hit her.

305
00:19:31,810 --> 00:19:33,308
Begin data capture.

306
00:20:06,261 --> 00:20:07,112
You okay?

307
00:20:07,793 --> 00:20:09,260
Where'd you learn to do that?

308
00:20:09,402 --> 00:20:12,006
Oh, I've just been taking
some Krav Maga classes, you know.

309
00:20:14,108 --> 00:20:15,845
Maybe we'll do this again sometime.

310
00:20:21,325 --> 00:20:22,905
Do we need to send backup?

311
00:20:23,385 --> 00:20:24,789
No, let them go.

312
00:20:25,129 --> 00:20:27,236
We have exactly what we need.

313
00:20:33,349 --> 00:20:34,853
Well, so, did they interrogate you?

314
00:20:35,306 --> 00:20:37,995
When I came to, there were a bunch
of people in the room but

315
00:20:38,956 --> 00:20:41,689
they didn't say a word to me.
They just sort of left me alone.

316
00:20:42,224 --> 00:20:44,080
Next thing I know,
you're kicking in the door.

317
00:20:45,843 --> 00:20:47,173
She got you good.

318
00:20:47,472 --> 00:20:48,636
Oh, it's cosmetic.

319
00:20:49,339 --> 00:20:50,173
It'll heal.

320
00:20:50,310 --> 00:20:52,403
Listen, you think it's safe
to make a call?

321
00:20:52,590 --> 00:20:54,667
I should probably
let my fiancée know I'm okay.

322
00:20:55,049 --> 00:20:56,377
Did you just say "fiancée"?

323
00:20:56,556 --> 00:20:57,373
Did I?

324
00:21:00,487 --> 00:21:01,713
Oh. I guess I did.

325
00:21:01,734 --> 00:21:02,553
Will!

326
00:21:02,607 --> 00:21:03,833
Do you remember that painter

327
00:21:04,473 --> 00:21:05,740
that I was gonna ask out?

328
00:21:05,860 --> 00:21:06,830
- Yeah.
- I...

329
00:21:06,847 --> 00:21:07,834
I asked her out.

330
00:21:07,919 --> 00:21:09,357
And what, you're getting married?

331
00:21:09,386 --> 00:21:11,197
Yeah. Well, no, not exactly.

332
00:21:11,380 --> 00:21:14,042
I was actually planning
on asking her last night

333
00:21:14,308 --> 00:21:16,786
before Anna interrupted.

334
00:21:16,957 --> 00:21:18,829
But I'm pretty sure she's gonna say yes.

335
00:21:18,978 --> 00:21:20,489
Oh, I can't believe this.

336
00:21:21,117 --> 00:21:23,531
How can you be marrying a girl
I haven't even met yet?

337
00:21:24,103 --> 00:21:25,361
Well, you know,

338
00:21:25,521 --> 00:21:27,364
I think the government-mandated
isolation

339
00:21:27,365 --> 00:21:28,943
might have something to do with it.

340
00:21:30,592 --> 00:21:32,533
Sydney, we haven't spoken in, like,
two years.

341
00:21:32,852 --> 00:21:34,634
What about you? What's been going on?

342
00:21:37,959 --> 00:21:40,314
For starters, I have a daughter.

343
00:21:41,336 --> 00:21:44,258
- What?
- Yeah, a baby girl.

344
00:21:44,466 --> 00:21:46,333
Her name is Isabelle.

345
00:21:48,642 --> 00:21:51,808
Sydney, are you kidding?
That's incredible.

346
00:21:52,552 --> 00:21:53,834
Who's the father?

347
00:21:55,510 --> 00:21:56,425
Vaughn.

348
00:21:58,550 --> 00:22:00,412
Vaughn, of course.

349
00:22:00,711 --> 00:22:02,772
You guys finally ended up together.

350
00:22:05,715 --> 00:22:07,264
<i>I hate lying to him.</i>

351
00:22:07,808 --> 00:22:10,208
He's my best friend.
I can't even tell him the truth.

352
00:22:11,893 --> 00:22:14,400
You should've seen Will's face
when I told him Vaughn was dead.

353
00:22:14,601 --> 00:22:15,520
Sydney,

354
00:22:15,929 --> 00:22:19,474
the only way to ensure Vaughn's safety
is to keep his existence a secret.

355
00:22:19,521 --> 00:22:22,227
- You did the right thing.
- That doesn't make it any easier.

356
00:22:22,312 --> 00:22:25,834
Will's abduction only underscores
our need for absolute vigilance.

357
00:22:26,073 --> 00:22:27,979
We're dealing with a very powerful
opponent.

358
00:22:28,490 --> 00:22:30,166
You think Prophet Five
had something to do

359
00:22:30,167 --> 00:22:31,062
with Will's abduction?

360
00:22:31,130 --> 00:22:33,955
There's no logical reason
anyone would abduct Will Tippin...

361
00:22:34,746 --> 00:22:36,380
unless they were trying to get to you.

362
00:22:46,207 --> 00:22:48,897
Relax. The operation is moving forward
as planned,

363
00:22:48,914 --> 00:22:51,382
and may I say that you have performed
admirably.

364
00:22:51,637 --> 00:22:53,271
The agreement was for Nadia's cure.

365
00:22:53,662 --> 00:22:56,913
Yes, once the operation is complete.

366
00:22:57,496 --> 00:22:59,819
If I'm to prepare for any unforeseen
circumstances,

367
00:22:59,854 --> 00:23:02,459
I need to know the full parameter
of what you've planned.

368
00:23:02,564 --> 00:23:04,228
All you need to do, Arvin,

369
00:23:04,703 --> 00:23:08,433
is task your team accordingly
when I give you the signal.

370
00:23:08,770 --> 00:23:10,370
And what exactly is the signal?

371
00:23:10,983 --> 00:23:11,842
Believe me,

372
00:23:12,055 --> 00:23:12,864
you'll know.

373
00:23:26,562 --> 00:23:28,451
This is Isabelle.

374
00:23:28,536 --> 00:23:29,718
Oh, Syd.

375
00:23:31,144 --> 00:23:33,080
- Sydney, she's beautiful.
- Thank you.

376
00:23:35,483 --> 00:23:38,036
Ma'am, would you like us
to stay on duty for the night?

377
00:23:38,070 --> 00:23:39,500
That won't be necessary.

378
00:23:39,908 --> 00:23:41,508
- You can go home.
- Thank you.

379
00:23:41,610 --> 00:23:42,938
The surveillance equipment's up.

380
00:23:42,979 --> 00:23:43,755
Thank you.

381
00:23:43,886 --> 00:23:44,652
See you.

382
00:23:45,316 --> 00:23:47,137
- You want to hold her?
- Really? Okay.

383
00:23:49,585 --> 00:23:50,415
Hey!

384
00:23:52,613 --> 00:23:53,430
Hey.

385
00:23:53,600 --> 00:23:54,519
I'm Will.

386
00:23:54,843 --> 00:23:56,278
What am I, like an uncle?

387
00:23:56,391 --> 00:23:57,481
- Uncle.
- Yeah.

388
00:23:57,796 --> 00:23:59,089
I'm uncle Will.

389
00:24:01,198 --> 00:24:03,390
Will, we were talking about
what happened.

390
00:24:03,964 --> 00:24:05,986
We have to assume you were grabbed

391
00:24:06,305 --> 00:24:08,135
because someone was trying to hurt me.

392
00:24:08,666 --> 00:24:09,730
Yeah? Well, yeah.

393
00:24:09,853 --> 00:24:13,043
I didn't think they wanted me for all
the Lakers statistics I have in my head.

394
00:24:13,138 --> 00:24:14,126
Right? No.

395
00:24:15,748 --> 00:24:17,237
It's... just...

396
00:24:18,767 --> 00:24:20,336
I'm sorry.

397
00:24:20,762 --> 00:24:23,129
None of this would have happened
if I wasn't in your life.

398
00:24:23,448 --> 00:24:25,523
Syd, stop. Are you kidding me right now?

399
00:24:25,709 --> 00:24:27,890
My life is so much better
because you're in it.

400
00:24:34,457 --> 00:24:36,022
ALERT! IDENTIFY DEVICE IMMEDIATELY

401
00:24:36,215 --> 00:24:37,758
Oh, what... Oh.

402
00:24:40,266 --> 00:24:41,070
What...

403
00:24:41,967 --> 00:24:43,577
- Sir? Hand over the baby.
- What?

404
00:24:43,726 --> 00:24:44,810
- Agent Rance...
- Ma'am,

405
00:24:44,839 --> 00:24:47,440
- take the baby from him right now.
- Okay, okay.

406
00:24:49,090 --> 00:24:49,774
What's going on?

407
00:24:50,936 --> 00:24:52,871
- Take it easy.
- What's going on? Hey!

408
00:24:54,418 --> 00:24:55,604
Sydney, what's going on?

409
00:24:55,686 --> 00:24:57,098
I don't know. I don't know.

410
00:25:02,475 --> 00:25:07,040
Well, it's a sub dermal device placed
just below the skull at the brain stem.

411
00:25:07,381 --> 00:25:09,357
I've never seen one this small before.

412
00:25:09,903 --> 00:25:12,354
It looks like they patched
a radio receiver

413
00:25:12,453 --> 00:25:14,148
to a powerful microcharge.

414
00:25:16,947 --> 00:25:18,436
So, what? What does that mean?

415
00:25:18,733 --> 00:25:20,494
It means that they... they...

416
00:25:21,086 --> 00:25:23,127
- put a bomb in your head.
- What?

417
00:25:23,358 --> 00:25:26,109
I know. I know. But there's good news.

418
00:25:26,241 --> 00:25:29,385
It looks like the charge is small enough
that the blast will be localized.

419
00:25:30,838 --> 00:25:31,612
Wait, wait.

420
00:25:31,694 --> 00:25:34,180
- So it might not kill me.
- Oh, no. It'll definitely kill you.

421
00:25:34,246 --> 00:25:35,925
There just won't be
any collateral damage.

422
00:25:36,007 --> 00:25:36,804
Marshall...

423
00:25:37,010 --> 00:25:38,266
How do we get it out of him?

424
00:25:38,535 --> 00:25:41,218
Well, we could perform
a surgical procedure, but...

425
00:25:41,729 --> 00:25:43,857
I'm worried there's
a gyroscopic fail-safe.

426
00:25:44,102 --> 00:25:46,884
I mean, there is a very real chance
that if we try to remove it,

427
00:25:48,120 --> 00:25:50,057
Will's head could explode.

428
00:25:50,183 --> 00:25:52,367
Get medical in here.
I want a full extraction scenario.

429
00:25:52,381 --> 00:25:54,894
What? No! Didn't you just hear
what he said about the exploding?

430
00:25:54,905 --> 00:25:55,595
Will, calm down.

431
00:25:55,604 --> 00:25:57,770
Sydney, how can I calm down?
There's a bomb in my head.

432
00:25:57,776 --> 00:25:58,850
Look, don't worry about it.

433
00:25:58,854 --> 00:26:00,390
We're gonna get it out of you. Just...

434
00:26:00,409 --> 00:26:01,310
What is that?

435
00:26:06,475 --> 00:26:07,430
It's my phone.

436
00:26:07,859 --> 00:26:09,306
It's just my phone.

437
00:26:11,520 --> 00:26:12,623
BLOCKED CALLER CALLING

438
00:26:12,746 --> 00:26:13,968
Am I supposed to answer this?

439
00:26:17,440 --> 00:26:18,212
Hello?

440
00:26:18,443 --> 00:26:19,579
<i>Hello, Sydney.</i>

441
00:26:20,221 --> 00:26:23,431
Now that I have your attention,
I have some demands.

442
00:26:26,347 --> 00:26:27,620
<i>Pay attention, Syd.</i>

443
00:26:29,910 --> 00:26:32,968
<i>You are going to need to do exactly
as you are told.</i>

444
00:26:33,319 --> 00:26:35,488
<i>You have access
to the government's</i>

445
00:26:35,639 --> 00:26:37,353
<i>Rambaldi archives at the D.S.R.</i>

446
00:26:37,582 --> 00:26:41,287
I'd like you to bring me
a particular page from his manuscript.

447
00:26:41,444 --> 00:26:42,444
Which one?

448
00:26:43,690 --> 00:26:44,690
Page 47.

449
00:26:45,343 --> 00:26:47,284
<i>I'm sure you're familiar with it.</i>

450
00:26:48,554 --> 00:26:50,357
There's a train leaving for Madrid

451
00:26:50,381 --> 00:26:53,249
from the Coimbra rail station
at 2100 tomorrow.

452
00:26:53,752 --> 00:26:55,214
<i>Be on it. Come alone.</i>

453
00:26:55,564 --> 00:26:58,218
<i>Once I have the manuscript page
in my possession,</i>

454
00:26:58,300 --> 00:27:01,036
I will give you the deactivation codes
for the bomb.

455
00:27:01,125 --> 00:27:05,575
- Anna, I swear to you...
<i>- Any deviation, Sydney,</i>

456
00:27:05,885 --> 00:27:08,708
and I'm afraid I'll have to blow up
your friend.

457
00:27:08,735 --> 00:27:09,735
<i>Bye now.</i>

458
00:27:11,819 --> 00:27:13,294
We have to take her threat seriously.

459
00:27:13,295 --> 00:27:16,044
Marcus, how quickly can you get
page 47 from the D.S.R.?

460
00:27:16,045 --> 00:27:17,645
I can have it within the hour.

461
00:27:17,646 --> 00:27:18,551
Do it.

462
00:27:18,552 --> 00:27:20,316
Of all the Rambaldi artifacts,

463
00:27:20,557 --> 00:27:22,145
why would she want page 47?

464
00:27:25,414 --> 00:27:26,503
Who's Rambaldi?

465
00:27:26,738 --> 00:27:29,720
Milo Rambaldi was a 15th century
visionary

466
00:27:29,767 --> 00:27:32,622
with an uncanny ability
to predict the future.

467
00:27:32,726 --> 00:27:36,081
His designs have prophesied everything
from binary code

468
00:27:36,139 --> 00:27:39,169
- to nuclear weaponry to...
- is that Sydney?

469
00:27:39,676 --> 00:27:42,937
Not exactly.
There are people that believe that's me.

470
00:27:44,586 --> 00:27:46,272
"Mulier hic picturata."

471
00:27:46,886 --> 00:27:49,297
"The woman pictured here,
the chosen one,"

472
00:27:49,686 --> 00:27:52,862
"will render the greatest power
unto utter desolation."

473
00:27:55,410 --> 00:27:57,008
You're "the chosen one"?

474
00:28:04,176 --> 00:28:06,450
You people really believe this stuff?

475
00:28:07,778 --> 00:28:11,110
We've... seen things that give
Rambaldi's words weight.

476
00:28:11,191 --> 00:28:14,593
Guys, can we debate this later...
after the bomb is out of my head?

477
00:28:14,594 --> 00:28:16,348
What's the harm in giving Anna the page?

478
00:28:16,383 --> 00:28:18,593
These are prophecies about things
I might do.

479
00:28:18,594 --> 00:28:20,493
If I don't do them, they're just words.

480
00:28:20,494 --> 00:28:22,309
That's right, Sydney, you have a point.

481
00:28:22,310 --> 00:28:23,957
Without you, that page is worthless.

482
00:28:23,958 --> 00:28:26,714
We're not seriously considering
giving into Anna's demands?

483
00:28:26,715 --> 00:28:28,600
- Yes, we--yes, we are.
- No, we're not.

484
00:28:28,647 --> 00:28:30,774
This page will get me close,
but there's no guarantee

485
00:28:30,775 --> 00:28:33,074
Anna will deactivate you
if we give her what she wants.

486
00:28:33,075 --> 00:28:35,091
Marshall, can you hack
the detonation frequency?

487
00:28:35,115 --> 00:28:37,921
Well, I mean, she mentioned
deactivation codes.

488
00:28:38,065 --> 00:28:39,793
The bomb and the detonator
are networked.

489
00:28:39,794 --> 00:28:42,143
I mean, maybe I could build a device
that would tap

490
00:28:42,144 --> 00:28:45,207
into the communication protocol,
reverse engineer the codes,

491
00:28:45,208 --> 00:28:47,214
but we would need to get the bomb

492
00:28:47,273 --> 00:28:50,289
within range of the detonator
in order for it to initialize.

493
00:28:50,324 --> 00:28:51,322
Get started on it.

494
00:28:51,364 --> 00:28:53,344
But... the only thing
I understood from that

495
00:28:53,379 --> 00:28:55,846
was to get the bomb
in range of the detonator?

496
00:28:55,881 --> 00:28:57,360
You ever been to Portugal?

497
00:29:05,825 --> 00:29:06,928
I'm sorry.

498
00:29:06,996 --> 00:29:08,466
It's simply not possible.

499
00:29:10,295 --> 00:29:12,295
There has been a terrible mistake.

500
00:29:12,854 --> 00:29:13,854
Look at me.

501
00:29:14,584 --> 00:29:17,643
I would not know how to purchase
a coach ticket if I tried.

502
00:29:17,678 --> 00:29:20,664
We demand a first-class cabin
at the front of the car.

503
00:29:20,665 --> 00:29:23,390
It is away from the commoners.

504
00:29:23,409 --> 00:29:25,182
